# Polyakovka, Uchalinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Polyakovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Polyakovsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 677 as of 2010. There are 11 streets.
Geography
Polyakovka is located 46&nbsp;km northeast of Uchaly (the district's administrative centre) by road. Komsomolsk is the nearest rural locality.
